AGI -&nbsp; One more day of contests at the Festival dell'Economia di Trento. First, towards the ministra for the Family, Christmas and Equal Opportunities and then the University. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Some twenty people were in front of the Palace of the Autonomous Province where the panel with host Eugenia&nbsp;Roccella was in progress. "Our bodies are not your propaganda," said a banner lying in Piazza Dante. "Evidently, there is a hostility that goes beyond the dispute with the government, there is hostility towards the world of motherhood," was the replica of the ministra. A little later a group of about 30 students of the Intifada collective of the University manifested in Piazza Dante in front of the palace of the Region in view of the arrival of Anna Maria&nbsp;Bernini. Students gathered under the slogan "Palestina libera", said they were there to "expect" the ministra.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2>Roccella, "denatility at the centre of government activity"></h2>
"We put the denatility at the centre of government action and we have allocated 1.5 billion with the first financial year and the second producing 16 billion direct and indirect benefits for families with very concrete measures," explained Roccella at the panel "Rearmo demographicgrafico alla Macron or choices aware of women?". The government, he added the ministra, moved "according to three axes, direct assistance, money in the pocket to families implementing the measure taken by the previous government and we increased the funds for the single check, are 3 billion more invested". The government continued to develop;Roccella, on average increased the cheque of approximately 700 euros a year. The second axis - it has explained - "is the conciliation and access to the work of women and the maintenance of the job, too many resign after the first or second son" and the third axis are the nurseries, on which is intervening also thanks to the funds of the Pnrr.
&nbsp;
"We want the implementation of the Family Centres: the next immediate step, even without waiting for the Financial, is to promote the centers for the family giving also specific tasks that they had not, because created without leaving the decision to the Regions - it has explained again Roccella -. We want them to be more: now they are between 500 and 600 concentrated in some regions, in others there are not at all, we want to multiply them, to invest at least 30 million and also other funds that must pass from the agreement State-Regions. We want to work on parental control, because apps already exist but need training because they are little used, grandparents and parents do not have sufficient training to activate these apps and know how to manage them. They will also serve to do drug training, such as Fentanyl, to give grandparents and parents the tools to understand alarm signals" he concluded.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Bernini, " &nbsp;40% of university students do not pay taxes"></h2>
"40 percent of the boys attend the university for free. This is welfare," said the Minister for University and Research, Anna Maria&nbsp;Bernini, who then, asked about the anti-Israel prayer held in Turin in an occupied faculty, added: "We can't turn universities into improper mosques." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"In Brussels - Bernini added - I went to say that we are the best place to host the third generation telescope. It is the possibility of bringing in Sardinia, inside a abandoned mine, the telescope that does not see but hears. We have been in Europe to say that we have the best place in the heart of the Mediterranean, in the heart of Barbagia". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"There are so many funds, but in Italy the problem is &nbsp; the continuity for research funds and this we have to work. I would like to make an appeal to the rectors. Let us not forget the European funds, because my greatest concern is what will happen since 2026. We are now dotted by the European funds of the Pnrr. Universities have never had so many funds, they are satolls." So the ministra Bernini who then added: "Especially after 2026 we must continue to make European programming. Now I have noticed that universities do not bands because they have too much money" and "the satiety of today is not obstacle for tomorrow. I wouldn't give up the Horizon funds now, because if we don't take them, they'll get some more. So make bands Horizon because that is the best way to use Europe."&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
